-- Aliansce Acquires Control of Five Brazil Shopping Malls for $313 Million
-- B y   K a r e n   E e u w e n s
-- 2012-01-10T08:48:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-10/aliansce-acquires-control-of-five-brazil-shopping-malls-for-313-million.html
Aliansce Shopping Centers SA (ALSC3) ,
Brazilâ€™s fourth-largest mall owner by market value,
agreed to buy control of five centers in the states of Rio de
Janeiro, Paraiba and Sao Paulo.  The value of the acquisitions is 574.5 million reais
($313.4 million), including 37.5 million reais of assumed debt,
according to a regulatory filing yesterday.  Following the deal, Aliansce will own all of Carioca
Shopping and Boulevard Campos, as well as 78 percent of Shopping
Taboao, 76.6 percent of Boulevard Campina Grande and 89 percent
of Caxias Shopping.  Aliansce will use credit lines of as much as 500 million
reais from  Banco Bradesco SA (BBDC4)  to help pay for the purchase.  To contact the reporter on this story:
